Classes in org.ndnx.ndn.protocol used by org.ndnx.ndn

          ContentNames consist of a sequence of byte[] components which may not be assumed to follow any string encoding, or any other particular encoding.

          Represents a NDNx data packet.
Interest
          Represents a NDN Interest packet, and performs all the allowed specializations of queries recognized and supported by them.

          A KeyLocator specifies where a content consumer or intermediary can find the public key necessary to verify a piece of content.

          NDN has a time representation for versions and signing times that is quantized at a granularity of 2^-12 seconds (approximately 1/4 msec).
